        "headline": "USN-8071-2: NSS vulnerability",
        "content": {
          "excerpt_text": "USN-8071-1 fixed a vulnerability in nss. This update provides the corresponding fix for Ubuntu 14.04 LTS, Ubuntu 16.04 LTS, Ubuntu 18.04 LTS, and Ubuntu 20.04 LTS. Original advisory details: It was discovered that NSS incorrectly handled memory when performing certain GHASH operations. A remote attacker could use this issue to cause NSS to crash, resulting in a denial of service, or possibly execute arbitrary code.",
          "lang": "en"
